        </linkGrp>
        <div n="239-07H1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1720.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-1" rend="align(center)">I.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-2" rend="flush left"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE bold encroachers on the deepGain by degrees huge tracts of land,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-3"> Till <hi rend="underline">Neptune</hi> with one gen'ral sweepTurns all again to barren strand.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="4" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-4" rend="align(center)">II.</l></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l n="5" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-5" rend="flush left">The multitude's capricious pranks&#13;Are said to represent the seas;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-6"> Which <hi rend="underline">breaking bankers</hi> and the <hi rend="underline">banks</hi>,Resume <hi rend="underline">their own</hi> whene'er they please.</l></lg><lg n="5" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-7" rend="align(center)">III.</l></lg><lg n="6" type="stanza"><l n="8" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-8" rend="flush left">Money, the life-blood of the nation,&#13;Corrupts and stagnates in the veins,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-9"> Unless a proper <hi rend="underline">circulation</hi>Its motion and its heat maintains.</l></lg><lg n="7" type="stanza"><l n="10" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-10" rend="align(center)">IV.</l></lg><lg n="8" type="stanza"><l n="11" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-11" rend="flush left">Because 'tis <hi rend="underline">lordly</hi> not to pay,<hi rend="underline">Quakers</hi> and <hi rend="underline">aldermen</hi> in state</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-12"> Like <hi rend="underline">peers</hi> have <hi rend="underline">levees</hi> ev'ry dayOf duns attending at their gate.</l></lg><lg n="9" type="stanza"><l n="13" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-13" rend="align(center)">V.</l></lg><lg n="10" type="stanza"><l n="14" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-14" rend="flush left">We want our money on the nail;&#13;The banker's ruin'd if he pays:</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-15"> They seem to act an ancient tale;The <hi rend="underline">birds</hi> are met to strip the <hi rend="underline">jays</hi>.</l></lg><lg n="11" type="stanza"><l n="16" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-16" rend="align(center) flush left">VI.</l></lg><lg n="12" type="stanza"><l n="17" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-17">Riches, the wisest monarch <ref target="#spp-239-07H1-footnote-1">1</ref><note place="foot" n="1" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-footnote-1"><hi rend="underline">Solomon</hi>.</note> sings,<hi rend="underline">Make pinions for themselves to fly</hi>:</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-18"> They fly like bats on <hi rend="underline">parchment wings</hi>,And geese their <hi rend="underline">silver</hi> plumes supply.</l></lg><lg n="13" type="stanza"><l n="19" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-19" rend="align(center)">VII.</l></lg><lg n="14" type="stanza"><l n="20" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-20" rend="flush left">No money left for squand'ring heirs!&#13;<hi rend="underline">Bills</hi> turn the lenders into debtors:</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-21"> The wish of <hi rend="underline">Nero</hi> now is theirs,That they <hi rend="underline">had never known their letters</hi><ref target="#spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">2</ref><note place="foot" n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">It is said of <hi rend="underline">Nero</hi>, that when he first came to the imperial dignity from the tutorage of <hi rend="underline">Seneca</hi>, that being asked to sign a warrant for an execution he wished he could not write.</note>.</l></lg><lg n="15" type="stanza"><l n="22" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-22" rend="align(center)">VIII.</l></lg><lg n="16" type="stanza"><l n="23" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-23" rend="flush left">Conceive the works of midnight hags,&#13;Tormenting fools behind their backs:</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-24"> Thus bankers o'er their bills and bagsSit squeezing <hi rend="underline">images of wax</hi><ref target="#spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">2</ref><note place="foot" n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">Witches were fabled to torment the absent by roasting or otherwise ill treating their images in wax.</note>.</l></lg><lg n="17" type="stanza"><l n="25" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-25" rend="align(center)">IX.</l></lg><lg n="18" type="stanza"><l n="26" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-26" rend="flush left">Conceive the whole enchantment broke;&#13;The witches left in open air,</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-27"> With pow'r no more than other folk,Expos'd with all their <hi rend="underline">magick</hi> ware.</l></lg><lg n="19" type="stanza"><l n="28" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-28" rend="align(center)">X.</l></lg><lg n="20" type="stanza"><l n="29" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-29" rend="flush left">So pow'rful are a banker's bills,&#13;Where creditors demand their due;</l><l n="30" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-30"> They break up counters, doors and tills,And leave the empty chests in view.</l></lg><lg n="21" type="stanza"><l n="31" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-31" rend="align(center)">XI.</l></lg><lg n="22" type="stanza"><l n="32" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-32" rend="flush left">Thus when an earthquake lets in light&#13;Upon the god of <hi rend="underline">gold</hi> and <hi rend="underline">hell</hi>,</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-33"> Unable to endure the sight,He hides within his darkest cell.</l></lg><lg n="23" type="stanza"><l n="34" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-34" rend="align(center)">XII.</l></lg><lg n="24" type="stanza"><l n="35" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-35" rend="flush left">As when a conj'rer takes a lease&#13;From <hi rend="underline">Satan</hi> for a terms of years,</l><l n="36" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-36"> The tenant's in a dismal case,Whene'er the <hi rend="underline">bloody bond</hi><ref target="#spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">2</ref><note place="foot" n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">These contracts were always supposed to be signed with blood.</note> appears.</l></lg><lg n="25" type="stanza"><l n="37" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-37" rend="align(center)">XIII.</l></lg><lg n="26" type="stanza"><l n="38" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-38" rend="flush left">A <hi rend="underline">baited</hi> banker thus desponds,From his own hand foresees his fall;</l><l n="39" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-39"> They have his <hi rend="underline">soul</hi>, who have his <hi rend="underline">bonds</hi>;'Tis like the <hi rend="underline">writing on the wall</hi><ref target="#spp-239-07H1-footnote-2">2</ref><note place="foot" n="2" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-footnote-2"><hi rend="underline">Mene mene tekel upharsin</hi>.</note>.</l></lg><lg n="27" type="stanza"><l n="40" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-40" rend="align(center)">XIV.</l></lg><lg n="28" type="stanza"><l n="41" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-41" rend="flush left">How will the caitiff wretch be scar'd,&#13;When first he finds himself awake</l><l n="42" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-42"> At the last trumpet, unprepar'd,And all his <hi rend="underline">grand account</hi> to make?</l></lg><lg n="29" type="stanza"><l n="43" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-43" rend="align(center)">XV.</l></lg><lg n="30" type="stanza"><l n="44" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-44" rend="flush left">For in that universal <hi rend="underline">call</hi>Few bankers will to heav'n be mounters;</l><l n="45" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-45"> They'll cry, <hi rend="underline">ye </hi>shops<hi rend="underline">, upon us fall</hi>,Conceal and <hi rend="underline">cover us, ye</hi> counters:</l></lg><lg n="31" type="stanza"><l n="46" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-46" rend="align(center)">XVI.</l></lg><lg n="32" type="stanza"><l n="47" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-47" rend="flush left">When <hi rend="underline">other</hi> hands the <hi rend="underline">scales</hi> shall hold,And they in <hi rend="underline">men and angels' sight</hi></l><l n="48" xml:id="spp-239-07H1-line-48"> Produc'd with all their bills and gold,<hi rend="underline">Weigh'd in the ballance, and found light</hi>.239-07H1   </l></lg></div>
